Model fitting varIdent models

Models that I considered have variance hererogeinity:

  • smf
  • below_biomass
  • wue
  • perc_n
  • ratio_c_n
  • Narea_g_m2
  • Nmass_mg_g
varident_response_vars <- response_vars[c("smf","below_biomass","wue","perc_n",
                                          "ratio_c_n", "Narea_g_m2","Nmass_mg_g")]
model_list_varident <- map(varident_response_vars, ~ mixed_model_2_varident(response = .x,
                                   varident_variable = "nfixer", 
                                   data = data_complete))
model_list_varident_2 <- map(varident_response_vars, ~ mixed_model_2_varident(response = .x,
                                   varident_variable = "treatment", 
                                   data = data_complete))
model_list_varident_3 <- map(varident_response_vars, ~ mixed_model_2_varident(response = .x,
                                   varident_variable = "nfixer_treatment", 
                                   data = data_complete))
model_list_varident_4 <- map(varident_response_vars, ~ mixed_model_2_varident(response = .x,
                                   varident_variable = "spcode", 
                                   data = data_complete))
AIC(lme(smf  ~ nfixer*treatment + init_height,
                                    random = ~ 1|spcode,
                                    method = "REML",
                                    #weights = varIdent(form = ~ c(1 | nfixer, 1 | treatment)),
                                    weights = varIdent(form = ~ 1 + treatment*nfixer | spcode ),
                                    data = data_complete))
[1] 607.016
rbind(as.data.frame(map(model_list_varident, AIC)),
      as.data.frame(map(model_list_varident_2, AIC)),
      as.data.frame(map(model_list_varident_3, AIC)),
      as.data.frame(map(model_list_varident_4, AIC))) %>% 
  add_column(varident_form = c("nfixer","treatment", "nfixer*treatment", "spcode")) %>% 
  select(varident_form, everything()) %>% 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, 2)  %>%
  datatable(class = 'cell-border stripe')
